[[File:Collection log detail.png|left|130px]]
The '''collection log''' is a [[book]] that players can receive from [[The Collector]] near the stairs in the [[Varrock Museum]]'s {{FloorNumber|uk=0}}. It records nearly every unique drop the player has obtained from various content in ''[[Old School RuneScape]]''. The player does not need to have claimed a collection log for it to start tracking drops.

Drops obtained prior to its release are '''not''' recorded for any player, excluding untradeable items (such as [[pet]]s) provided that they can be tracked by the game; for example, [[long bone]]s the player had traded to [[Barlak]] or buried before the log's release were not added to it, but any long bones in the player's possession were added.

Each entry in the log is tracked by the item itself, not where it was obtained. For example, obtaining a [[dragon pickaxe]] from the [[Chaos Elemental]] will also log it under other bosses that drop it, such as [[Callisto]] and the [[King Black Dragon]].

There is a cap on the amount each item can be tracked, depending on the item in question. For example, [[Zulrah's scales]] will only be tracked up to 65,535 and [[Bracelet of ethereum|bracelets of ethereum]] up to 250.

It can be stored in a [[bookcase]] within a [[player-owned house]], and can also be accessed from the adventurer's log within a player's [[Achievement Gallery]].

As of {{UD|Below Ice Mountain|an update}} on [[14 April]] [[2021]], there are a total of 1,513 slots to fill in the collection log, with a total of 1,351 unique entries being tracked. Pets, [[gilded equipment]], and [[3rd age equipment]] account for 110 of the 152 slots containing duplicate items.

[[File:Collection log interface.png|thumb|right|310px|The collection log interface.]]
